# Change Quality Gate

Prefer conventional engineering checks over ritual “natural-language Excel”
test tables. Do not invent tests that only freeze wording.

## By change type

| Change | Quality bar |
| ------ | ----------- |
| Skill / reference **prose** (roles, policy, workflow copy) | List files + intent → edit → `npm run check`. No `toContain` on markdown. Optional human skim. |
| Skill **scripts** / lint helpers | Real I/O + exit codes under `tests/python/` (or project equivalent). |
| TypeScript / MCP tool behavior | Vitest (or project suite): `ok`, codes, schema, structured fields — not skill body phrases. |
| Agent follows long skill text | LLM evals if/when the repo has them — **not** required in CI today. |

## Forbidden

- Fake acceptance matrices that only restate documentation sentences.
- Locking `SKILL.md` / `references/**` prose with snapshot/`toContain` tests (see `skill-testing.mdc`).

## Still do

- Analyze and confirm approach before large edits when the user wants planning.
- Name files to touch and the outcome for each todo.
- For **behavioral** code: prefer tests that exercise real inputs/outputs; run the gate after edits; use timeouts and non-interactive flags.
